  ('balance-beam-walk', 'Balance Beam Walk narrows the base of support and raises the precision demand without needing heavy load. The athlete must regulate visual focus, foot placement, rhythm, and posture the way a gymnast does on a beam.', 'Belongs in Movement Intelligence because the main adaptation is learning and controlling balance positions while fresh, not accumulating fatigue. Slot: beam_balance.', 'Use in Movement Intelligence while the athlete is fresh and attentive. Place before tumbling, jumping, or fatigue blocks; do not use raised/narrow surfaces when tired.', 'Do not use raised beams, complex turns, or hopping when the athlete is tired or fearful. Beam balance is precision practice, not a conditioning station.', 'Scale one variable at a time: base width, visual input, range, speed, surface height, perturbation, external load, hold duration, or reset time. Progress only when the athlete can pause, breathe, and repeat the same alignment on both sides.'),
